Pre-Game Insights: Mitchell Marsh will be leading the Aussies in the T20I series.
Glenn Maxwell is in the squad and fit to face the West Indies.
Rovman Powell-led side will look to bounce after a disappointing ODI series.
Former skipper Jason Holder and hard-hitter Kyle Mayers are in the 15-man squad.
Others: Australia are fourth in the ICC T20 Rankings.
West Indies are seventh in the ICC men's T20I rankings.
The 1st T20I between Australia and West Indies is scheduled to be played on February 9, 2024, Friday, at 1:30 PM IST.
The 1st T20I between Australia and West Indies will be played at Bellerive Oval in Hobart.
All three Australia vs West Indies T20I matches will be broadcast on Star Sports 2, Star Star Sports 1 Hindi and their respective HD channels in India.
Disney+ Hotstar will be streaming Australia vs West Indies, T20I Series, live, online.
